## Scope

This slice establishes the live MVU loop end-to-end so U2ŌĆōU8 extend a proven
pattern rather than inventing one. It adds the Elmish host packages, authors the
root model/message/dispatcher in a new `Shell.fs`, mounts the Elmish program from
`MainWindow`, rewrites the shell view to switch on panel id, renders **one**
read-only panel (`stack`) to prove the read path, and stands up the headless UI
test project plus the `ui-smoke` gate. U1 is gating and MUST land first; it is a
prerequisite for every other part. For U1 only the `stack` panel renders real
content; the other four panel ids render a titled placeholder until their part
lands.

## Requirements

### R-1. U1.1 ŌĆö Add the Elmish host packages

The implementation MUST add `Avalonia.FuncUI.Elmish` and `Elmish`
`PackageReference` entries to **both** `OpticalConstructor.Ui.fsproj` and
`OpticalConstructor.App.fsproj`, version-aligned with the pinned
`Avalonia.FuncUI` 1.6.0 / `Avalonia` 11.3.4 already present. No other package
may be added in U1.

### R-2. U1.2 ŌĆö Author the root model, message, and dispatcher in a new `Shell.fs`

The implementation MUST add a new module
`OpticalConstructor.Ui/Shell.fs` (new) holding the root MVU surface. `Shell.fs`
MUST live in the `OpticalConstructor.Ui` project (not the App project) so the
headless UI test project can mount it without launching the desktop App. It MUST
define:

- A `Page` discriminated union with exactly the two cases `Construction` and
  `SynthesisFit`, matching the two `navEntry` modules.
- A `RootModel` record aggregating the existing sub-models. The minimal field
  set required by this arc is: the loaded `UserEnvironment.EnvironmentSettings`
  (theme + panel layout); the current `Page`; `ConstructionPage.Model`
  (`ConstructionPage.fs:106`); `Workspace.Model` (`Workspace.fs:32`); an
  optional `SynthesisFitPage.Model` (`SynthesisFitPage.fs:46`, opened on demand);
  `ChartSettings.ChartSettings`
  (`Berreman/OpticalConstructor/OpticalConstructor.Ui/Charts/ChartSettings.fs:50`);
  `Readout.Markers`
  (`Berreman/OpticalConstructor/OpticalConstructor.Ui/Charts/Readout.fs:15`); and
  the `MaterialLibrary`
  (`Berreman/OpticalConstructor/OpticalConstructor.Domain/MaterialLibrary.fs:47`,
  seeded from `MaterialLibrary.standard`). The model MUST NOT hold any field
  forbidden by ┬¦0.5.
- A `RootMsg` discriminated union that wraps each existing sub-`Msg`
  (`Construction of ConstructionPage.Msg`, `Workspace of Workspace.Msg`,
  `Fit of SynthesisFitPage.Msg`, `Source of SourceEditorView.SourceMsg`) plus
  the new shell-level cases this arc adds incrementally (`Shell` for
  navigation/theme/panel-show/dock, `Chart` for chart-settings/cursor edits,
  `Io` for open/save/new/template/gallery). A part MUST add only the `RootMsg`
  cases it wires; U1 MUST add at minimum the `Construction`, `Workspace`, and
  `Shell` cases.
- A root `init : RootModel * Cmd<RootMsg>` and a root
  `update : RootMsg -> RootModel -> RootModel * Cmd<RootMsg>`. `update` MUST be a
  dispatcher: each case calls the matching existing sub-`update`
  (e.g. `ConstructionPage.update` `ConstructionPage.fs:173`, `Workspace.update`
  `Workspace.fs:52`, `SynthesisFitPage.update` `SynthesisFitPage.fs:107`,
  `SourceEditorView.update` `SourceEditorView.fs:59`) and re-wraps the result,
  attaching a `Cmd` only for the effectful transitions enumerated in Part U2 /
  U7 / U8. U1's `update` attaches `Cmd.none` to every case (no effects yet).

### R-3. U1.3 ŌĆö Mount the Elmish program from `MainWindow`

The implementation MUST replace the static mount at `Program.fs:39` with an
`Avalonia.FuncUI.Elmish` program:
`Program.mkProgram Shell.init Shell.update Shell.view |> Program.withHost <hostControl> |> Program.run`,
mounted from the existing `MainWindow` (`Program.fs:33`). `Shell.init` MUST seed
`RootModel.env` from the already-loaded `Startup.settings` (`Program.fs:29`,
`UserEnvironment.load`) so the persisted theme/layout still drive the first
frame. The themeŌåÆAvalonia seam in `Initialize` (`Program.fs:48`,
`AppShell.themeVariant`) MUST be left in place.

### R-4. U1.4 ŌĆö Rewrite the shell view to switch on panel id and render real panels

`AppShell.shellView`/`panelView` (`AppShell.fs:118`/`:98`) MUST be rewritten (or
superseded by a `Shell.view` that calls into a panel-dispatching helper) to take
the `RootModel` and the `dispatch : RootMsg -> unit`, switch on the panel id
string, and render the corresponding panel view. The visible/ordered panel set
MUST keep coming from the existing pure reducers `AppShell.visiblePanels`
(`AppShell.fs:75`), `setPanelVisible` (`AppShell.fs:60`), and `dockPanel`
(`AppShell.fs:68`); dock edges keep mapping through the existing `toDock`
(`AppShell.fs:86`). For U1 only the `stack` panel renders real content; the
other four ids render a titled placeholder until their part lands.

### R-5. U1.5 ŌĆö Render the stack panel read-only to prove the loop

The `stack` panel view MUST render the selected node's layer rows from the
existing presentation helper `StackEditor.layerRowLabels`
(`Berreman/OpticalConstructor/OpticalConstructor.Ui/StackEditor.fs:217`), with
thickness strings from `StackEditor.displayThickness` (`StackEditor.fs:210`),
fed from `RootModel.construction`. U1 wires no edit dispatch; it proves the
read path end-to-end.

### R-6. U1.6 ŌĆö Add the `ui-smoke` gate

The implementation MUST add `.gates/OpticalConstructor/ui-smoke.gates` (new), a
command gate that launches the app on the **Avalonia headless platform**
(`Avalonia.Headless`) and asserts the smoke test in U1.7 passes. It MUST follow
the existing gate schema (`name`, `description`, `kind: command`, `command`,
`pass_when.exit_code: 0`, `runtime_estimate_seconds`, `tags`, `applies_to`,
`qualifier`). The `command` MUST run the headless smoke test in the new UI test
project (U1.7) filtered to the smoke trait, e.g.
`dotnet test <UI.Tests.fsproj> -c Release --filter Category=ui-smoke`.

### R-7. U1.7 ŌĆö Create the headless UI test project and the smoke test

The implementation MUST add a new test project
`OpticalConstructor/OpticalConstructor.Ui.Tests/OpticalConstructor.Ui.Tests.fsproj`
(new), referencing `OpticalConstructor.Ui` and using `Avalonia.Headless` +
`Avalonia.Headless.XUnit` (xUnit, matching the existing
`OpticalConstructor.Tests` framework `xunit.v3`). The headless Avalonia
dependency MUST stay out of the pure `OpticalConstructor.Tests` project so
`constructor-unit-tests` stays Avalonia-free. The new project MUST be registered
in `Berreman/Berreman.slnx` (edit). The **smoke test** (trait `Category=ui-smoke`)
MUST: start the app/host on the headless platform, assert the window opens and
`OnFrameworkInitializationCompleted` ran (`Program.fs:50`), assert each
panel/page view **instantiates and renders one frame without throwing**, then
shut the host down.

Also create the `.gates/OpticalConstructor/ui-tests.gates` gate file (per ┬¦0.7;
the UI test project exists once this slice lands, so `ui-tests` is enforceable
from this slice forward) and at least one per-panel headless view test (the
`stack` panel view test) so the `ui-tests` gate has a passing test set.

### R-8. U1.8 ŌĆö Native-host adapters MUST degrade gracefully under headless

Because the headless platform (and a machine without the WebView2 Evergreen
runtime) cannot host `WebView2` or an OpenTK GL surface, every native-host
adapter (Part U3/U4/U5/U8) MUST render a placeholder "unavailable" surface
rather than throw when its runtime is absent, so the `ui-smoke` gate renders a
frame for every panel headlessly. This is a hard requirement of the smoke gate,
not a stretch goal. For U1, the four non-`stack` panels render titled
placeholders, which already satisfy "render one frame without throwing."

## Non-requirements

- Does NOT make the `stack` panel editable (U2 / slice 003 wires `EditStack`).
- Does NOT wire the materials, sources, chart, or results panel content (U3ŌĆōU6).
- Does NOT add the renderer-host adapters `ChartHosts.fs` (slice 002 / Part U5).
- Does NOT add any effectful `Cmd`; U1's `update` attaches `Cmd.none` to every case.
- Does NOT add any package other than `Avalonia.FuncUI.Elmish` + `Elmish`.
- Does NOT touch the deferred clone-swap decision (┬¦0.2) or invent drag-to-redock chrome (┬¦0.3).
- Does NOT edit any frozen core module (┬¦0.1).

