## Testing plan

Gates that apply to this slice (run in order; first failure short-circuits):
`build`, `unit-tests`, `constructor-unit-tests`, `impl-log-structure`,
`state-of-world-structure`, `ui-smoke`, `ui-tests`.

- `build` (`Berreman/`): `dotnet build Berreman.slnx -c Release` succeeds with the
  two new package refs resolved and `OpticalConstructor.Ui.Tests` in the solution
  (AC-U1.4).
- `constructor-unit-tests`: the pure `OpticalConstructor.Tests` suite stays
  Avalonia-free and green (the headless dependency lives only in the new
  `OpticalConstructor.Ui.Tests` project).
- `ui-smoke`: headless host opens, `OnFrameworkInitializationCompleted` runs,
  every panel/page view renders one frame without throwing (AC-U1.3).
- `ui-tests`: the `stack`-panel headless view test passes; this slice creates the
  `ui-tests.gates` file and the UI test project on which it depends.
- `unit-tests` (BerremanTests core): no core module changes; the suite stays at
  or above the prior baseline (count_at_least, baseline 0 on the first slice).

Worker fills in concrete assertions; reuse `OpticalConstructor.Tests` model
helpers for model-state assertions.

## Risks

- **High: foundational + gating.** This slice stands up the entire MVU loop, the
  Elmish host mount, the headless test project, and two new gates from scratch.
  Every later slice depends on the `Shell.fs` surface and the `ui-smoke` gate, so
  a wrong shape here forces wide re-work. Concrete worries: (a) version-aligning
  `Avalonia.FuncUI.Elmish` / `Elmish` against the pinned FuncUI 1.6.0 / Avalonia
  11.3.4; (b) keeping the headless Avalonia dependency out of the pure
  `OpticalConstructor.Tests` project so `constructor-unit-tests` stays
  Avalonia-free; (c) ensuring the four placeholder panels and any native-host
  adapter render one frame headlessly without throwing (┬¦U1.8).

## Hand-off

- The `RootModel`/`RootMsg`/`Shell.init`/`Shell.update`/`Shell.view` surface and
  the panel-id dispatch in `AppShell`/`Shell.view` are the proven pattern U2ŌĆōU8
  extend. Later parts add only the `RootMsg` cases and effectful `Cmd`s they wire.
- The `ui-smoke` gate and the `OpticalConstructor.Ui.Tests` project exist from
  this slice forward; every later slice keeps `ui-smoke` and `ui-tests` green and
  adds its own per-panel view test.
- `ChartHosts.fs` (the AvaPlot / WebView2 / Canvas renderer-host adapters) is NOT
  built here; it lands in slice 002 (Part U5) and is reused by the materials,
  sources, results, and lifecycle slices.
- The worker MUST emit the state-of-the-world file with a fenced YAML block whose
  top-level key is `gates:` carrying this round's baseline counts (e.g.
  `berreman_unit_tests`, plus the constructor / ui-smoke / ui-tests passing
  counts) so the next slice's `count_at_least` gates have a baseline. Example:

  ```yaml
  gates:
    berreman_unit_tests: <int>
  ```
